.SH NAME
dotty-env-list - List the credential names in a namespace.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdotty env list [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Print the key names stored in the namespace, one per line, sorted. Values are
never printed — use get, use, or run to read them.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for list


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--namespace\fP="default"
	credential namespace to operate on

.PP
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile to operate on (defaults to the active profile)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  dotty env list --namespace=aws
.EE


